<section xml:id="objects-arrays_vocabulary">
<title>Vocabulary</title>
<ul>
<li>
<title>pseudocode:</title>
<p>
<idx><h>pseudocode</h></idx>
A way of designing programs by writing rough drafts in a combination of English and Java.</p></li>
<li>
<title>helper method:</title>
<p>
<idx><h>helper method</h></idx>
A method that implements part of a more complex algorithm; often it is not particularly useful on its own.</p></li>
<li>
<title>top-down design:</title>
<p>
<idx><h>top-down design</h></idx>
Breaking down a problem into subproblems, and solving each subproblem one at a time.</p></li>
<li>
<title>selection sort:</title>
<p>
<idx><h>selection sort</h></idx>
A simple sorting algorithm that searches for the smallest or largest element <m>n</m> times.</p></li>
<li>
<title>merge sort:</title>
<p>
<idx><h>merge sort</h></idx>
A recursive sorting algorithm that divides an array into two parts, sorts each part (using merge sort), and merges the results.</p></li>
<li>
<title>off-by-one:</title>
<p>
<idx><h>off-by-one</h></idx>
A common programming mistake that results in iterating one time too many, or too few.</p></li>
<li>
<title>static context:</title>
<p>
<idx><h>static context</h></idx>
The parts of a class that run without reference to a specific instance of the class.</p></li>
<li>
<title>collection:</title>
<p>
<idx><h>collection</h></idx>
A Java library class, like <c>ArrayList</c>, that represents a group of objects.</p></li>
<li>
<title>wrapper method:</title>
<p>
<idx><h>wrapper method</h></idx>
A method that calls another method without doing much additional work.</p></li>
</ul>
</section>
